---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Annotation Operations" active="annotation-ops" section="architecture">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">Annotation Operations</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero-title">From paragraph intent to pipeline action.</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-lede">
        This lane turns reading decisions into reusable intelligence. Every marker and instruction moves through a
        durable queue, lands in a structured chapter file, and becomes available to AI assistants, search, and future
        automation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="stack">
    <h2>The operating path</h2>
    <div class="ops-flow">
      <div class="ops-node">
        <h3>1) Reader workbench</h3>
        <p>Paragraph hover activates the right-hand workspace. Markers and notes are captured immediately.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ops-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="ops-node">
        <h3>2) Queue ledger</h3>
        <p>Action instructions accumulate in a local queue and can be copied as one execution set.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ops-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="ops-node">
        <h3>3) Durable chapter file</h3>
        <p>One click sync writes a chapter-level JSON handoff with markers, notes, and the full queue text.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ops-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="ops-node">
        <h3>4) Pipeline intelligence</h3>
        <p>Classification and queued actions feed extraction, verification, augmentation, and future auto-marking.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="stack">
    <h2>Three scopes, one queue</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card card-tight">
        <strong>Paragraph</strong>
        <p class="small">Fine-grained edits, doctrinal tags, and contextual research tied to one location.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card card-tight">
        <strong>Book</strong>
        <p class="small">Structural instructions that apply across chapters in the same title.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card card-tight">
        <strong>Global</strong>
        <p class="small">Reusable production rules for style, quality checks, and guardrails across titles.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="stack">
    <h2>What this unlocks next</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="card card-tight">
        <strong>Auto-marking from learned patterns</strong>
        <p class="small">As pattern density grows, the pipeline can pre-label likely esoteric or reality sections before author review.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card card-tight">
        <strong>Cross-book retrieval</strong>
        <p class="small">Any queued insight can be reused in later books, audits, and interactive assistant sessions.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card card-tight">
        <strong>Cost-efficient execution packs</strong>
        <p class="small">Batch copy of accumulated instructions reduces repeated prompting and keeps work sessions focused.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card card-tight">
        <strong>Planner-aware auto views</strong>
        <p class="small">When annotation lanes expand in the plan, the dashboard sync flow can detect and create missing architecture views.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .ops-flow {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr;
      gap: 10px;
      align-items: stretch;
    }
    .ops-node {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: var(--card);
      padding: 14px;
    }
    .ops-node h3 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .ops-node p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .ops-arrow {
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    @media (max-width: 1100px) {
      .ops-flow {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
      .ops-arrow {
        transform: rotate(90deg);
        margin: -4px 0;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
